The paper deals with the problem of constructing geometric spanners, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The spanners are constructed for unit disk graphs, which are commonly used in wireless ad-hoc networks (cs.NI). The paper also presents a distributed algorithm, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The algorithm has a linear time complexity, which suggests that it may involve data structures (cs.DS) and combinatorial optimization (cs.DM) techniques.
